<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-22597] Jira possible error when using jira url ending with /</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-22597</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I encountered an issue when I was testing Jira extension (from CQ) with the real Jira server.&lt;br/&gt;
If I use jira-url in format `&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080&lt;/a&gt;`, all goes well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But if I use url as `&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/&lt;/a&gt;`. there is an error during an issue CRUD operation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that it would be better if camel-Jira was able to handle both formats (which worked before &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/commit/4ea43935a64e409e1f40be35a71fdc72c49c4805&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;commit&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
